modules.description: Handles incoming HTTP and WebSocket connections by setting up a stream socket listener, applying configuration, and routing requests through a websocket connection handler. Processes socket addresses and stream sockets, integrating with Eio for asynchronous I/O. Manages error handling and connection lifecycle within a switch context.

Handles WebSocket connections with custom error and message handling, supporting configuration, switch management, and resource-specific communication. Operates on stream sockets, nonces, hostnames, ports, and resource paths. Used to establish and manage real-time data exchanges in networked applications.

Handles WebSocket protocol negotiation and communication, including parsing upgrade headers, managing frame encoding/decoding, and establishing bidirectional data streams. Operates on byte sequences, buffers, and network connections. Used to implement real-time client-server interactions, such as live chat or collaborative editing interfaces.

manages HTTP and WebSocket connections by binding to socket addresses, handling request routing, and managing asynchronous I/O through Eio. It supports custom error handling, message processing, and lifecycle management for stream sockets and WebSocket sessions. Key data types include socket addresses, stream sockets, nonces, hostnames, ports, and resource paths. It enables real-time communication by establishing and maintaining WebSocket connections with specific resources.
